From: Miro Mraz <mraz.miro@seznam.cz>
Subject: [PATCH 0/2] Pixel 4a (sunfish): enable FTM5 touchscreen on mainline

This series sits on top of David Heidelberg's v4 stmfts5 series
(20260409-stmfts5-v4-0-64fe62027db5@ixit.cz on linux-input). Both fixes
were found while bringing up the touchscreen on a Google Pixel 4a
(sunfish, FTM5CU56AA1BE, chip ID 0x4836) running postmarketOS with the
sm7150-mainline 7.1-rc3 kernel.

PATCH 1: Bumps the stmfts_reset post-deassert delay from 50 ms to 500 ms.
FTM5 firmware boot includes internal CRC verification of flash sections
and consistently takes ~300 ms before the chip's I2C state machine is
up. 50 ms causes stmfts5_configure's I2C read to fail with -ENXIO
silently (only the dev_dbg 'initializing...' line surfaces in dmesg).
Diagnosed via ftrace function_graph + funcgraph-retval. A follow-up
could replace the fixed sleep with a poll loop on STMFTS_READ_ALL_EVENT.

PATCH 2: Adds the sunfish DTS node. Two non-obvious bits:
  - vreg_touch_en (regulator-fixed on pm6150 GPIO 4) models the
    downstream load-switch arrangement so the regulator framework
    keeps the chip powered across probe-failure-and-retry cycles.
  - mode-switch-gpios uses GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW (not HIGH). Empirically,
    driving the line HIGH puts the chip into SLPI-routed mode where
    the AP-side I2C address goes silent. LOW keeps it on the AP path.

Tested on Pixel 4a. After the series boots, /dev/input/event2 ("stmfts")
appears and reports MT_B touch events with correct X/Y inside the
1080x2340 panel range.

Signed-off-by: Miro Mraz <mraz.miro@seznam.cz>

